==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quintilllion
<hw>Quin*till"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed fr. L.
<ets>quintus</ets> the fifth, after the analogy of <ets>million</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>quintillion</ets>. See <er>Quint</er>.]</ety> <def>According
to the French notation, which is used on the Continent and in America,
the cube of a million, or a unit with eighteen ciphers annexed;
according to the English notation, a number produced by involving a
million to the fifth power, or a unit with thirty ciphers annexed. See
the Note under <er>Numeration</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quintin</ent>⟦br⟧
